Discussion
The results confirmed the superiority of the Point Transformer model over traditional models in semantic segmentation tasks. The findings also demonstrated the importance of the Attention layer and Positional Encoding in improving performance. Nevertheless, further efforts are required to expand the Saudi dataset and strengthen semantic integration within HBIM systems.
Conclusion
This research proposed an integrated framework for automated documentation and preservation of Saudi heritage using AI-driven HBIM technologies. Point Transformer networks demonstrated strong effectiveness in semantic segmentation tasks, opening opportunities for large-scale applications in heritage management. However, further experiments on local datasets are necessary to ensure robustness and generalizability.
Future Work
1. Develop a comprehensive multi-modal Saudi heritage dataset.
2. Conduct broader quantitative experiments and comparisons with state-of-the-art models.
3. Integrate HBIM with Digital Twin platforms.
4. Develop interactive 3D visualization tools.
5. Apply the framework at a national scale in collaboration with heritage authorities.
